a/commons/f/fd/Death_Valley_Scenic_Byway_-_Charcoal_Kilns_in_Death_Valley_-_NARA_-_7717912.jpg","cap":"Death Valley Scenic Byway Charcoal Kilns in Death Valley","desc":"Snow dusts a line of charcoal kilns in Death Valley. During silver and Borax mining in the 1800s, these kilns were used to turn pinon pine to coal to run the smelters at the Modoc Mine. Location: California (36.246° N 117.076° W) Status: Public domain. Photo from National Park Service","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Death_Valley_Scenic_Byway_-_Charcoal_Kilns_in_Death_Valley_-_NARA_-_7717912.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/5a/Death_Valley_Scenic_Byway_-_Golden_Canyon_-_NARA_-_7717935.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/5a/Death_Valley_Scenic_Byway_-_Golden_Canyon_-_NARA_-_7717935.jpg","cap":"Death Valley Scenic Byway Golden Canyon","desc":"The sun begins to light up Golden Canyon, bringing out the rich tones of the rock. Location: California Status: Public domain. Photo from National Park Service","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Death_Valley_Scenic_Byway_-_Golden_Canyon_-_NARA_-_7717935.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/c7/Death_Valley_Scenic_Byway_-_Golden_Canyon_in_Death_Valley_-_NARA_-_7717936.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/c7/Death_Valley_Scenic_Byway_-_Golden_Canyon_in_Death_Valley_-_NARA_-_7717936.jpg","cap":"Death Valley Scenic Byway Golden Canyon in Death Valley","desc":"Best when viewed in the afternoon, Golden Canyon's namesake is realized when its golden hues are brought out by sunshine. Location: California Status: Public domain. Photo from National Park Service","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Death_Valley_Scenic_Byway_-_Golden_Canyon_in_Death_Valley_-_NARA_-_7717936.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/54/Death_Valley_Scenic_Byway_-_Gower_Gulch_-_NARA_-_7717937.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/54/Death_Valley_Scenic_Byway_-_Gower_Gulch_-_NARA_-_7717937.jpg","cap":"Death Valley Scenic Byway Gower Gulch","desc":"Late afternoon casts sunrays over the muted yellows and oranges of Gower Gulch. Location: California (36.411° N 116.832° W) Status: Public domain. Photo from National Park Service","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Death_Valley_Scenic_Byway_-_Gower_Gulch_-_NARA_-_7717937.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/f/f4/Death_Valley_Scenic_Byway_-_Layers_of_Rock_in_the_Narrows_of_Mosaic_Canyon_-_NARA_-_7717980.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/f/f4/Death_Valley_Scenic_Byway_-_Layers_of_Rock_in_the_Narrows_of_Mosaic_Canyon_-_NARA_-_7717980.jpg","cap":"Death Valley Scenic Byway Layers of Rock in the Narrows of Mosaic Cany","desc":"Layers of earth and sediments comprise the stripey walls of Mosaic Canyon. Location: California Status: Public domain. Photo from National Park Service","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Death_Valley_Scenic_Byway_-_Layers_of_Rock_in_the_Narrows_of_Mosaic_Canyon_-_NARA_-_7717980.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/1/1c/Death_Valley_Scenic_Byway_-_Leadfield_Dugout_-_NARA_-_7717941.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/1/1c/Death_Valley_Scenic_Byway_-_Leadfield_Dugout_-_NARA_-_7717941.jpg","cap":"Death Valley Scenic Byway Leadfield Dugout","desc":"This stone, dirt and wood dugout in Leadfield is evidence of past lead mining in Death Valley. Location: California (36.898° N 116.829° W) Status: Public domain. Photo from National Park Service","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Death_Valley_Scenic_Byway_-_Leadfield_Dugout_-_NARA_-_7717941.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/5a/Death_Valley_Scenic_Byway_-_Looking_Across_the_Black_Mountains_-_NARA_-_7717918.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/5a/Death_Valley_Scenic_Byway_-_Looking_Across_the_Black_Mountains_-_NARA_-_7717918.jpg","cap":"Death Valley Scenic Byway Looking Across the Black Mountains","desc":"The curves and hills of the Black Mountains can be captured from a high peak above known as Dante's View. Location: California (36.218° N 116.729° W) Status: Public domain. Photo from National Park Service","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Death_Valley_Scenic_Byway_-_Looking_Across_the_Black_Mountains_-_NARA_-_7717918.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/9c/Death_Valley_Scenic_Byway_-_Lower_Furnace_Creek_Wash_-_NARA_-_7717942.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/9c/Death_Valley_Scenic_Byway_-_Lower_Furnace_Creek_Wash_-_NARA_-_7717942.jpg","cap":"Death Valley Scenic Byway Lower Furnace Creek Wash","desc":"Dark, rough terrain makes up the landscape of Lower Furnace Creek Wash. Location: California Status: Public domain. Photo from National Park Service","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Death_Valley_Scenic_Byway_-_Lower_Furnace_Creek_Wash_-_NARA_-_7717942.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/0c/Death_Valley_Scenic_Byway_-_Manly_Beacon_-_NARA_-_7717943.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/0c/Death_Valley_Scenic_Byway_-_Manly_Beacon_-_NARA_-_7717943.jpg","cap":"Death Valley Scenic Byway Manly Beacon","desc":"Named after a legendary gold seeker William Manly, who helped his party survive being lost in Death Valley, Manly Beacon is located at Golden Canyon. Location: California (36.424° N 116.826° W) Status: Public domain. Photo from National Park Service","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Death_Valley_Scenic_Byway_-_Manly_Beacon_-_NARA_-_7717943.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/60/Death_Valley_Scenic_Byway_-_Manly_Beacon_-_NARA_-_7717945.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/60/Death_Valley_Scenic_Byway_-_Manly_Beacon_-_NARA_-_7717945.jpg","cap":"Death Valley Scenic Byway Manly Beacon","desc":"A lovely view of Manly Beacon can be seen from the Badlands. Location: California (36.423° N 116.824° W) Status: Public domain. Photo from National Park Service","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Death_Valley_Scenic_Byway_-_Manly_Beacon_-_NARA_-_7717945.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/60/Death_Valley_Scenic_Byway_-_Manly_Beacon_-_NARA_-_7717969.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/60/Death_Valley_Scenic_Byway_-_Manly_Beacon_-_NARA_-_7717969.jpg","cap":"Death Valley Scenic Byway Manly Beacon","desc":"Manly Beacon, towering over the Furnace Creek Badlands, served as a natural compass for lost miners. Location: California Status: Public domain. Photo from National Park Service","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Death_Valley_Scenic_Byway_-_Manly_Beacon_-_NARA_-_7717969.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/f/f4/Death_Valley_Scenic_Byway_-_Manly_Beacon_-_NARA_-_7717974.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/f/f4/Death_Valley_Scenic_Byway_-_Manly_Beacon_-_NARA_-_7717974.jpg","cap":"Death Valley Scenic Byway Manly Beacon","desc":"Manly Beacon was named after two men named Manly and Rogers who hiked 500 miles to Los Angeles and back to get help for stranded emigrants in Death Valley. Location: California Status: Public domain. Photo from National Park Service","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Death_Valley_Scenic_Byway_-_Manly_Beacon_-_NARA_-_7717974.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/30/Death_Valley_Scenic_Byway_-_Manly_Beacon_at_Golden_Canyon_-_NARA_-_7717944.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/30/Death_Valley_Scenic_Byway_-_Manly_Beacon_at_Golden_Canyon_-_NARA_-_7717944.jpg","cap":"Death Valley Scenic Byway Manly Beacon at Golden Canyon","desc":"The gold-hued Manly Beacon contrasts brilliantly with the blue sky at Golden Canyon. Location: California Status: Public domain. Photo from National Park Service","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Death_Valley_Scenic_Byway_-_Manly_Beacon_at_Golden_Canyon_-_NARA_-_7717944.jpg"}]}